                   "message":  "SCENE-WORLD-BRIDGE: promote scene path resolver into rge-scene-loader\n\nLift the editor-binary-private `.rge-project` / `.rge-scene` path\nresolver out of `rge-editor` into the production `rge-scene-loader`\ncrate, so any caller can load a scene path into a `World` without\nre-implementing project resolution. Unblocks in-app scene Open\n(follow-up). Pure substrate; no behaviour change to `--scene`.\n\n- rge-scene-loader: add `pub fn load_scene_world_from_path(\u0026Path) -\u003e\n  Result\u003cWorld, SceneWorldLoadError\u003e` (file_name extension dispatch +\n  project first-scene resolution + read + RON parse) plus a CLI-neutral\n  thiserror `SceneWorldLoadError` that wraps the existing `SceneLoadError`\n  via `Loader(_)` — the loader error boundary is preserved, not broadened.\n  `load_scene_into_world` + `SceneLoadError` are unchanged.\n- rge-editor: delete the local `SceneLoadCliError` enum + `Display` +\n  `load_scene_world_from_path`; the `--scene` branch now calls\n  `rge_scene_loader::load_scene_world_from_path` (same one-line-stderr +\n  ExitCode::FAILURE posture). Drop the now-unused `rge-data` + `ron` deps.\n  Refresh two stale doc comments.\n- Move the golden-project-success + unsupported-extension tests into\n  crates/rge-scene-loader/tests/scene_path_loader.rs.\n\nruntime-headless, editor-shell, and rge-data are untouched (the rge-data\nidentity-only test is a schema-local test, not a duplicate of the loader).\n\nCodex pre-execution review: APPROVED\n(ai_handoffs/SCENE-WORLD-BRIDGE_REVIEW_2026-05-29_19-36-34+0300.md).\n\nCo-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.8 (1M context) \u003cnoreply@anthropic.com\u003e",
